== Notes ==
* {{note label|Note 1|a|a}} Sources give the date of the robbery as either 13 June 1907{{sfn|Brackman|2000|p=58}}{{sfn|Shub|1960|p=227}} or 26 June 1907,{{r|Bombs Kill Many}}{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=3}} depending on whether [[Old Style and New Style dates|Old Style]] [[Julian calendar]] or New Style [[Gregorian calendar]] dates are used. The Russian government used the Julian calendar until February 1918 when it switched to the Gregorian calendar by skipping thirteen days in that year so that 1 February 1918 was followed by 15 February 1918.{{sfn|Christian|1997|p=6}} For purposes of this article, dates are provided according to Gregorian calendar dates.
* {{note label|Note 2|b|b}} Joseph Stalin used a variety of names during his lifetime. His original Georgian name was "Josef Vissarionovich Djugashvili", but his friends and family called him "Soso".{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=xxxi}}{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=23}} During his early revolutionary years, which would include the years of the 1907 Tiflis bank robbery, he mostly went by the revolutionary [[nom de guerre]] "Koba", which he obtained from a character in [[Alexander Kazbegi|Alexander Kazbegi's]] novel ''[[The Patricide]]''.{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=xxxi}}{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=63}} He published poetry under the name "Soselo".{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=xxxi}} In 1912, he began to use the name Stalin and later adopted this as his surname after October 1917.{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=xxxi}} The name Stalin is translated to mean "Man of [[Steel]]."{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=xxxi}}{{sfn|Sebag Montefiore|2008|p=268}} This article uses the name by which he is most commonly known to the world, "Joseph Stalin", for clarity.

