{{Infobox language |name = Asaro'o |altname = Morafa |states = [[Papua New Guinea]] |region = [[Madang Province]] |ethnicity = |speakers = {{sigfig|1250|2}} |date = 2003 |ref = e18 |familycolor = Papuan |fam1 = [[Trans–New Guinea languages|Trans–New Guinea]] |fam2 = [[Finisterre–Huon languages|Finisterre–Huon]] |fam3 = [[Finisterre languages|Finisterre]] |fam4 = [[Warup languages|Warup]] |iso3 = mtv |glotto = mole1240 |glottorefname = Molet–Asaro'o }}
'''Asaro'o''', or '''Morafa''', is one of the [[Finisterre languages]] of [[Papua New Guinea]]. Molet may be a dialect or a closely related language.
