{{Unreferenced|date=December 2013}}
The '''Gav-Paradhi''' are one of the [[Pardhi|Paradhi]] [[Tribe]]s of [[India]]. Unlike the other Paradhi tribes they were not classed as a '[[Denotified Tribes|Criminal Tribe]]' by the [[British Raj]] government, under [[Criminal Tribes Act]] 1871. This was because unlike the other Paradhi tribes like the [[Phase Pardhi]], the Gav-Paradhi had become settled agriculturalists.

The Gav-Paradhi live primarily in the [[Amravati District]].

